oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: John Buchanan
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Portrait of John David Buchanan (1876-1944), a lifelong Clay County resident and contractor for the Clay County courthouse.
He and his brother built the Clay County Courthouse in 1870. They were the contractors.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
